Steve and Jen are the sweetest and most gorgeous souls and I had the best time capturing their engagement photos at @mintroomstudios. Just look at those smiles!! Sara and Hammad’s Nikkah and Rukhsati is live on the blog!! {Link is in my profile!} I have been looking forward to Sara and Hammad’s wedding ever since photographing their engagement session last year, and their wedding was such a delight to be part of, kicking off with their Nikkah and Rukhsati!! Sara and Hammad are such sweethearts and are a total joy to be around. I loved how they were laughing and giggling the entire day. Sara wore a beautiful pistachio green outfit and Hammad rocked a white sherwani which really brightened up the winter day and they were absolutely GLOWING during their portraits. Head to the link in my profile to see more from this beautiful and heartfelt Nikkah!!

Come see Sara and Hammad’s elegant winter Walima Reception on the blog! {Link is in my profile!} Sara and Hammad really prioritized making sure their guests enjoyed their reception which I just loved! They had a bubble tea station, an epic sparkler and dry ice entrance, and games to get all the guests involved. They played a version of musical chairs where guests had to find a specified object around the room and make it back before all the chairs were filled. It was such a fun and hilarious game to watch! Head to the link in my profile to see more!!! Also doesn’t Sara look like an absolute princess mA!? 😍

This beautiful engagement session is live on the blog!! (Link is in my profile to check it out!) Manar and Yasser both live in the states, but are having their reception here in Toronto since Yasser’s family lives here. We weren’t sure if we’d be able to fit in their engagement session before their wedding, but thankfully these two were coming in for just a couple of days for some wedding prep and we were able to squeeze it in. Not only do Manar and Yasser have the cutest smiles, they also have amazing style!!! Both of Manar’s dresses were so magical and she looked like a princess- especially in that gold dress! We got the most beautiful glowy sunset light which made their images even dreamier. Head to the blog to see more dreamy magic!!! Manar and Yasser, I’m so excited to see you again at your wedding iA!!
